CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1958, pg. 10A, reads:"Renee's Staff-Here is part of the staff of instructors at Renee's Dance Studio, scheduled to hold its grand opening Sunday, Sept. 14, in Terrace Room of the Terrace Hall Hotel. Left to right: Gladys Beverly, hostess and receptionist; Alberta Thompson, ballet and interpretative dancing, and Renee Young, better known to Pittsburghers as Florence Wright, proprietor. - Harris Photo - Adv."
TitMainTitle: Three women seated in wooden chairs, including Alberta Thompson in center, and Florence Wright [Renee Young] on right wearing sleeveless top and long strand of beads, holding cigarette, in restaurant or club in basement?
